<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 3:54PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF NORTHWESTERN MORTON
AND NORTH CENTRAL GRANT COUNTIES THROUGH 430 PM CDT/330 PM MDT/...
At 354 PM CDT/254 PM MDT/, a strong thunderstorm was located 7 miles
northeast of Heart Butte Dam, or 39 miles south of Beulah, moving
northwest at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Glen Ullin around 410 PM CDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Hebron.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
